		"cooperatingInstitutions": [],
		"projects": [],
		"countryDescription": "CLaDA-BG consortium consists of leading research and teaching institutions in Bulgaria, public libraries, museums, and archives. It represents DARIAH as well as the CLARIN research infrastructures on a national level and conducts various activities in the fields of Digital Arts and Humanities and Natural Language Processing. It aims at creating networks of data and of researchers working on them in order to establish an information infrastructure for the storage and representation of local linguistic, historical, cultural, and artistic patrimony, putting it in an internationally relevant context and providing instruments for the investigation of contemporary language and society against its background.\r\n<h3>Key areas of activities</h3>\r\nLanguage Resources and Technologies, Cultural Heritage, Ontologies, Linked Open Data and Knowledge Graphs, Data Mining, Storage and Management, Big Data, 3D technology for DH, Cooperation with Cultural and Educational Institutions, National and International Networking and Collaboration in NLP and DH, Teaching Materials in DH and NLP, Open Science",
		"countryLogo": "https://www.dariah.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/CLADABG_logo.png"
	},
