		"countryDescription": "The national infrastructure has four areas of key actions. Firstly, it focuses on sharing digital resources, providing access to registries, thesauri, datasets and metadata. Secondly, it works towards providing tools and services for supporting the entire life cycle of digital arts and humanities, investing also on education and training activities. Finally, it supports communities of practice by promoting standards and best practices, engaging in dialogue on theoretical and methodological issues; and\r\nencouraging community engagement activities.\r\n<h4>National priorities</h4>\r\n• to support the Greek arts and humanities communities and to contribute to the development of research using information technologies\r\n• to broaden the scope of research through the interconnection of distributed digital resources of various kinds\r\n• to promote the access, use, creation and long-term preservation of research data in digital form\r\n• to support the exchange of knowledge, methods and work practices among scholarly communities",
